originalText.text: Small but ample seating to suit the space. The layout and acoustics really lend the room to a speakeasy feel. It doesnâ€™t accommodate large crowds which I find attractive. The bartenders/host were friendly and carried on a lively conversation with patrons seated at the bar. They were very skilled in mixing the Blue Quarterâ€™s signature cocktails. I had the Marteani and Oolong Island Ice Tea. Both were unique and delicious. We spent about an hour and a half there but I could easily spend 2+ hrs alone sipping and reading a book. originalText.text: Happened to eat nearby the area and found this place. This cocktail place is very close to be like a speakeasy where it's inside a blue door that is inside a restaurant. Behind the blue door you'll see a bar in a small room with maybe 8 seats. It wasnt crowded around like 7ish and the atmosphere was nice and quite spacious. The cocktails menu priced at $15 each and had interesting blends. I ordered the "studio 60" drink and thought it was really interesting because it has carrot inside. However sadly I didn't taste any of that and the coriander chutney was super strong. Made me feel like I was actually eating food. The drink after a few more sips as the ice dilutes was quite nice. It was an interesting drink as I never experienced something like that before...
